on guide ✅ Bookmark practice test portal STEP 3: Study Environment Setup [20 min] Physical Setup: 🖥️ Primary screen: Laptop/desktop for video lectures 📱 Secondary screen: Tablet/phone for textbook reference 📝 Notebook: Handwrite key concepts (improves retention by 23%) ⏱️ Timer: Pomodoro app for 90-min deep work blocks 🎧 Noise-cancelling headphones: Eliminate distractions 💧 Water + snacks: Cognitive fuel (almonds, dark chocolate, green tea) Digital Setup: 📊 Spreadsheet tracker: Daily progress monitoring (I'll create this below) 📅 Calendar blocks: 8AM-8PM study sessions locked in 🚫 App blockers: Block social media 8AM-8PM (Freedom, Cold Turkey) 📧 Email autoresponder: \"Studying for certification, available after 8PM\" STEP 4: Course Reconnaissance [15 min] Quick preview before deep study: ✅ Scan full curriculum table of contents ✅ Count total modules/chapters (typically 15-20 chapters) ✅ Note chapter lengths (pages/video minutes) ✅ Identify \"heavy\" chapters (more content) vs \"light\" chapters ✅ Watch welcome video (orientation to course structure) 📚 PHASE 2: 2-WEEK INTENSIVE STUDY PROTOCOL ⏰ OPTIMIZED DAILY SCHEDULE (8AM-8PM) TIME BLOCK\tACTIVITY\tTECHNIQUE\tDURATION 8:00-8:30 AM\t☕ Morning activation\tReview yesterday's notes, preview today's modules\t30 min 8:30-10:00 AM\t🧠 Deep work block 1\tNEW content (video lectures + textbook reading)\t90 min 10:00-10:15 AM\t🚶 Break\tWalk, stretch, hydrate\t15 min 10:15-11:45 AM\t🧠 Deep work block 2\tNEW content continuation\t90 min 11:45 AM-12:00 PM\t📝 Active recall\tWrite down everything from memory (no notes)\t15 min 12:00-1:00 PM\t🍽️ Lunch + rest\tEat away from desk, mental break\t60 min 1:00-2:30 PM\t🧠 Deep work block 3\tNEW content\t90 min 2:30-2:45 PM\t🚶 Break\tMovement, hydrate\t15 min 2:45-4:15 PM\t🧠 Deep work block 4\tNEW content\t90 min 4:15-4:30 PM\t📝 Active recall\tMemory dump exercise\t15 min 4:30-4:45 PM\t🚶 Break\tStretch, snack\t15 min 4:45-6:15 PM\t🔁 Review + consolidate\tFlashcards, quizzes, practice questions\t90 min 6:15-6:30 PM\t🚶 Break\tShort walk\t15 min 6:30-7:30 PM\t🎯 Application practice\tWatch coaching session videos, role-play scenarios\t60 min 7:30-8:00 PM\t📊 Daily review + planning\tUpdate tracker, plan tomorrow, spaced repetition\t30 min Total Study Time: 12 hours/day Total Break Time: 2.5 hours built-in 📅 OPTIMIZED 14-DAY BREAKDOWN WEEK 1: FOUNDATION MASTERY DAY\tPRIMARY FOCUS\tMODULES/CHAPTERS\tMILESTONES\tHOURS Day 1 (Mon)\tWhat is Health Coaching + Structure\tModules 1-2\tComplete orientation, understand coaching framework\t12 hrs Day 2 (Tue)\tCoaching Process Part 1\tModule 3 (Part A)\tMaster coaching relationship building\t12 hrs Day 3 (Wed)\tCoaching Process Part 2\tModule 3 (Part B)\tMaster behavior change theory, motivational interviewing\t12 hrs Day 4 (Thu)\tWhole Person Health Part 1\tModule 4 (Part A)\tNon-communicable diseases, exercise, nutrition\t12 hrs Day 5 (Fri)\tWhole Person Health Part 2\tModule 4 (Part B)\tSleep, stress, holistic wellness\t12 hrs Day 6 (Sat)\tEthics + Legal + Review\tModule 5 + Week 1 consolidation\tComplete all content, master ethical guidelines\t12 hrs Day 7 (Sun)\tWeek 1 Integration\tFull review, flashcards, practice test 1\tTake Practice Test #1 (target: 70%+)\t12 hrs WEEK 2: MASTERY + EXAM PREP DAY\tPRIMARY FOCUS\tACTIVITIES\tMILESTONES\tHOURS Day 8 (Mon)\tWeak area reinforcement\tReview Practice Test 1 mistakes, deep dive weak topics\tIdentify knowledge gaps\t12 hrs Day 9 (Tue)\tCoaching application mastery\tWatch ALL ACE coaching session videos, practice scenarios\tMaster real-world application\t12 hrs Day 10 (Wed)\tFull content review cycle\tSpeed review all modules, flashcard intensive\tConsolidate all knowledge\t12 hrs Day 11 (Thu)\tPractice test intensive\tPractice Test #2 (target: 80%+), review mistakes\tAchieve passing score\t12 hrs Day 12 (Fri)\tFinal weak spot elimination\tFocus ONLY on remaining weak areas\tAchieve 90%+ confidence\t12 hrs Day 13 (Sat)\tExam simulation day\tFull simulated exam environment, time yourself\tAchieve 85%+ readiness\t12 hrs Day 14 (Sun)\tCERTIFICATION EXAM\tMorning: Light review. Afternoon: TAKE EXAM\tPASS & GET CERTIFIED ✅\t4 hrs study + exam 🧠 OPTIMIZED LEARNING TECHNIQUES 1. Active Recall (30% of study time) What: Test yourself WITHOUT looking at notes How to implement: After each 90-min block: Write everything from memory on blank paper Use Anki/Quizlet flashcards (create as you go) Teach concepts out loud to imaginary student Record yourself explaining topics, play back to identify gaps Science: Retrieval practice improves retention by 200% vs re-reading 2. Spaced Repetition (20% of study time) Optimal review schedule: Day 1: Learn new content Day 2: Review Day 1 content (morning activation) Day 4: Review Day 1 content again (evening consolidation) Day 7: Review Day 1 content (week integration) Day 14: Review Day 1 content (pre-exam) Tools: Anki app (automated spaced repetition) Physical flashcard rotation system Daily review checklist 3. Interleaving (15% of study time) What: Mix different topics in one session (vs blocking) How: Don't study Module 1 → Module 2 → Module 3 linearly Study: Module 1 → Module 3 → Module 2 → Module 4 Mix coaching techniques with health content Alternate between theory and application Science: Improves discrimination between concepts and long-term retention 4. Elaborative Interrogation (15% of study time) What: Constantly ask \"WHY?\" and \"HOW?\" How: Read statement: \"Motivational interviewing uses open-ended questions\" Ask: WHY does it use open-ended questions? Answer: Because they encourage client exploration vs yes/no Ask: HOW does this differ from directive coaching? Continue until deep understanding 5. Feynman Technique (10% of study time) What: Explain complex concepts in simple language Steps: Choose concept (e.g., \"Transtheoretical Model of Change\") Explain it to a 12-year-old (out loud or written) Identify gaps where explanation breaks down Go back to source, re-learn Simplify explanation further 6. Visual Mapping (10% of study time) What: Create visual diagrams of relationships Examples: Mind maps of coaching process flow Timelines of behavior change stages Comparison tables (health coach vs nutritionist vs trainer) Flowcharts of ethical decision-making Tools: Hand-drawn (best for retention) MindMeister, Coggle (digital options) 📊 DA"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=54a192db-ca10-49f7-8f93-6370e081c0f9","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=54a192db-ca10-49f7-8f93-6370e081c0f9"}]}]}]
